Egypt Stocks: Egyptian Resorts, Orascom Construction Industries

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-06-23T13:31:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/egypt-stocks-egypt-for-poultry-and-heliopolis-housing.html
Egypt ’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30) 
advanced for the first time in four days, gaining 0.1 percent to
5,479.6 at the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo. The measure lost 1.1
percent this week.  The following shares rose or fell in Cairo. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Egypt for Poultry (EPCO)   fell 1 percent to 2.95 Egyptian
pounds, the lowest level in more than three weeks. The Cairo-
based chicken producer’s board of directors approved raising
provisions by 2.36 million pounds ($396,000) after settling a
tax dispute with the government.  Egyptian Resorts Co. (EGTS)   rose for the first time in
three days, gaining 2.7 percent to 1.16 pounds. Misr Insurance
Co. transferred 73.04 million shares of its holding in Egyptian
Resorts to one of its subsidiaries, the resort developer’s
investor relations manager Abu Bakr Makhlouf said by telephone.  Orascom Construction Industries (OCIC)   snapped a three-
day decline, rising as much as 1.2 percent before closing 0.5
percent higher at 274.07 pounds. The nation’s biggest publicly
traded builder had its share-price estimate raised to 281 pounds
from 286.6 pounds at Cairo-based investment bank Beltone
Financial Holding SAE.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
